FM Spokesman Comments on APEC Meeting
BEIJING , November 19 ( Xinhua ) -- China 's Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang said at a weekly news conference today that the sixth Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation ( APEC ) informal meeting has shown the determination to solve the region 's difficulties through cooperation .
He said that the declaration issued at the end of the two-day meeting in Kuala Lumpur was for a concerted effort by APEC members to get out of the current difficulties .
They also passed the APEC Agenda on Science and Technology Industry Cooperation for the 21st Century , proposed by Chinese President Jiang Zemin , and the APEC Action Program on Skills Development , as proposed by Malaysia .
Tang said that Jiang put forward a three-point proposal on stepping up international cooperation , restructuring and improving the international financial system , and respecting the different choices of countries .
Jiang also announced at the meeting the establishment of a 10-million-U.S . - dollar China APEC Science and Technology Industry Cooperation Fund and the China APEC Enterprises Assembly .
Tang said that APEC leaders discussed ways of dealing with the Asian financial crisis , restructuring the international financial system , advancing trade and investment liberalization , and strengthening economic and technological cooperation .
These discussions help promote mutual understanding and cooperation , he said .
